# AI Video Studio — Environment Variables
# =========================================
# Set these in AWS Amplify → App Settings → Environment Variables
#
# Only NEXT_PUBLIC_* variables are exposed to the browser.
# All other secrets (GPU keys, service role keys, DB passwords)
# are stored server-side in Supabase Edge Function secrets.

# ─── FRONTEND (set in Amplify) ─────────────────────────────────────
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://ixinimgdzqhizphaczjx.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJzdXBhYmFzZSIsInJlZiI6Iml4aW5pbWdkenFoaXpwaGFjemp4Iiwicm9sZSI6ImFub24iLCJpYXQiOjE3ODQzMTg5NzcsImV4cCI6MjA5OTg5NDk3N30.zib-8ya2X2IUGmjgZ1J6OrgiSi-VXzDOPKXGPE284-I

# ─── SERVER-SIDE (already set in Supabase Edge Function secrets) ───
# These are NOT needed in Amplify. They're stored securely in Supabase:
#   GPU_SERVER_URL      → GPU server tunnel URL
#   GPU_SERVER_API_KEY  → API key for GPU server auth
#   SUPABASE_URL        → auto-provided to Edge Functions
#   SUPABASE_ANON_KEY   → auto-provided to Edge Functions
#   SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY → auto-provided to Edge Functions